Package au.csiro.pathling.library.io.sink

Class DataSinkBuilder

java.lang.Object
au.csiro.pathling.library.io.sink.DataSinkBuilder
public class DataSinkBuilder extends Object
This class knows how to take an @link{EnumerableDataSource} and write it to a variety of different targets.

  • Method Details

    • ndjson

      public void ndjson(@Nullable String path, @Nullable String saveMode)
      Writes the data in the data source to NDJSON files, one per resource type and named using the "ndjson" extension.
      Parameters:
      path - the directory to write the files to
      saveMode - the save mode to use:
      • "error" - throw an error if the files already exist
      • "overwrite" - overwrite any existing files
      • "append" - append to any existing files
      • "ignore" - do nothing if the files already exist

    • ndjson

      public void ndjson(@Nullable String path, @Nullable String saveMode, @Nullable UnaryOperator<String> fileNameMapper)
      Writes the data in the data source to NDJSON files, one per resource type and named using a custom file name mapper.
      Parameters:
      path - the directory to write the files to
      saveMode - the save mode to use:
      • "error" - throw an error if the files already exist
      • "overwrite" - overwrite any existing files
      • "append" - append to any existing files
      • "ignore" - do nothing if the files already exist
      fileNameMapper - a function that maps a resource type to a file name

    • parquet

      public void parquet(@Nullable String path, @Nullable String saveMode)
      Writes the data in the data source to Parquet files, one per resource type and named using the "parquet" extension.
      Parameters:
      path - the directory to write the files to
      saveMode - the save mode to use:
      • "error" - throw an error if the files already exist
      • "overwrite" - overwrite any existing files
      • "append" - append to any existing files
      • "ignore" - do nothing if the files already exist

    • delta

      public void delta(@Nullable String path)
      Writes the data in the data source to a Delta database. Any existing data in the Delta files will be overwritten.
      Parameters:
      path - the directory to write the files to

    • delta

      public void delta(@Nullable String path, @Nullable String importMode)
      Writes the data in the data source to a Delta database. Existing data in the Delta files will be dealt with according to the specified ImportMode.
      Parameters:
      path - the directory to write the files to
      importMode - the import mode to use, "overwrite" will overwrite any existing data, "merge" will merge the new data with the existing data based on resource ID

    • tables

      public void tables()
      Writes the data in the data source to tables within the Spark catalog, named according to the resource type.

      Any existing data in the tables will be overwritten.

    • tables

      public void tables(@Nullable String importMode)
      Writes the data in the data source to tables within the Spark catalog, named according to the resource type. Existing data in the tables will be dealt with according to the specified ImportMode.
      Parameters:
      importMode - the import mode to use, "overwrite" will overwrite any existing data, "merge" will merge the new data with the existing data based on resource ID

    • tables

      public void tables(@Nullable String importMode, @Nullable String schema)
      Writes the data in the data source to tables within the Spark catalog, named according to the resource type and prefixed with the provided schema name. Existing data in the tables will be dealt with according to the specified ImportMode.
      Parameters:
      importMode - the import mode to use, "overwrite" will overwrite any existing data, "merge" will merge the new data with the existing data based on resource ID
      schema - the schema name to write the tables to
